cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on solving rearrangement planning problems with a real robotic arm. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is also likely as the paper relies on visual inputs from a camera to guide the rearrangement planning. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another likely category as the paper proposes an AlphaGo-like strategy for improving the efficiency of Monte-Carlo Tree Search. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also possible as the paper uses a policy trained from rearrangement planning examples to improve the efficiency of MCTS. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is less likely but still possible as the paper presents a closed-loop rearrangement framework that can recover from errors and external perturbations.
